# Reverse-proxy + automatic HTTPS for self-hosted "notes".
#
# APP_ORIGIN (from .env, e.g. https://notes.yourdomain.com) is the only thing to
# set. Caddy obtains and renews a Let's Encrypt certificate for that hostname and
# proxies everything — including WebSocket upgrades — to the app container.
#
# Requirements: ports 80 + 443 reachable from the internet and the DNS A/AAAA
# record for the hostname pointing at this host.
{$APP_ORIGIN} {
	reverse_proxy notes:3000
}
